{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1783811224,"nonce":"gK872sjrmrPVJ0l3bPAeCDh3rco=","title":"A backend-neutral package containing a structural general cast whose target type is lossy on a DIFFERENT backend does not round-trip when that package is deployed cross-dialect (the epic's H2: extract from one dialect, deploy to another).","message":"Surfaced by codex during f982b68 PR B (general CAST inversion). After that PR, a general `CAST(x AS ty)` in a check / generated / index / view-body expression lowers to a structural `ExprNode::Cast { ty }`. PostgreSQL renders `numeric(p, s)` faithfully, so a PG-introspected check `CAST(x AS numeric(10, 2))` becomes `Cast { ty: Decimal { precision: 10, scale: 2 } }` in the package. Two cross-dialect problems when that package is published to MySQL or SQLite:\n\n1. **Silent precision loss.** MySQL/SQLite `write_cast_type` render every `Decimal` as a bare `DECIMAL`/`NUMERIC` (dropping the scale), so the deployed cast changes semantics (`CAST(x AS DECIMAL(10,2))` -\u003e `CAST(x AS DECIMAL)`).\n2. **Perpetual churn.** MySQL/SQLite introspection reads that bare `DECIMAL`/`NUMERIC` back and the lowering guard (added in PR B) keeps it `Raw`, while the desired side remains a structural `Cast{Decimal}` -\u003e the check/generated/view expression reports changed on every plan. `I128` casts (bare `numeric` / `DECIMAL(65,0)`) have the same structural-vs-`Raw` mismatch cross-dialect.\n\nNOTE: this was already broken before PR B (a PG `numeric(10,2)` cast was `Raw`-verbatim and simply invalid MySQL cast syntax at DDL exec). f982b68's H1 exit (a squealy-published schema re-plans to empty on the SAME backend) is met and correct — the lowering guard keeps a Decimal/I128 cast `Raw` on the backend that renders it lossy, so same-backend flows never produce a lossy structural cast.\n\nA proper fix needs one of:\n- **Context-aware render rejection**: reject a structural GENERAL cast whose type a backend cannot represent faithfully (MySQL/SQLite Decimal-with-scale, I128) at check/render time, failing loud instead of silently. `write_cast_type` currently cannot distinguish a general cast from a result pin (where bare `DECIMAL` is correct because the precision lives in the view's output column type), so this needs the rendering context threaded through.\n- **A package cross-dialect validation pass** that rejects an unrepresentable cast for the target backend before publishing.\n- **Precision-preserving cast rendering** on MySQL/SQLite where possible.\n\nScope: `crates/squealy-parse/src/lower.rs` (`general_cast` guard), the backend `write_cast_type` renderers, and/or a `check_create`-time validation. Belongs to the epic's Phase 4 (H2: arbitrary external DBs + cross-dialect deploy). Relates to acb1c6d and f982b68.","files":null}]}